WEBVTT

00:01.401 --> 00:03.369
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on</i> Grey's Anatomy:

00:03.403 --> 00:06.770
The Chief's under the spell
of some insane man in camouflage.

00:06.806 --> 00:08.933
Major Owen Hunt.
I'm a trauma surgeon.

00:10.043 --> 00:11.772
You're reading your mom's diary?

00:11.811 --> 00:13.642
I'm not half the surgeon my mother was.

00:13.680 --> 00:15.614
Chief wants us
to give George one of our interns?

00:15.648 --> 00:20.415
You didn't even think to ask for me?
Screw you, Dr. O'Malley.

00:21.788 --> 00:25.485
We can take it slow.
Maybe just... first base.

00:34.401 --> 00:36.494
Meredith.

00:36.536 --> 00:39.528
- I'm only opening one box.
- Plan was not to open any.

00:39.572 --> 00:41.699
The plan was to take
the boxes to the attic.

00:41.741 --> 00:44.437
Look, it's Anatomy Jane.

00:44.477 --> 00:47.241
<i>For a surgeon,</i>
<i>every patient is a battlefield.</i>

00:47.280 --> 00:50.408
- I'll never have my own office.
- <i>They're our terrain,</i>

00:50.450 --> 00:54.716
<i>where we advance, retreat,</i>
<i>try to remove all the landmines.</i>

00:54.754 --> 00:57.780
- And she still has her little twosh.
- Her what?

00:57.824 --> 00:59.985
Anatomy Jane had detachable organs.

01:00.026 --> 01:03.086
I could never remember the real names,
so I made up names.

01:03.129 --> 01:06.064
Like the twosh was next to the chubbel.

01:06.099 --> 01:09.000
And that was connected to the slivvy.

01:09.636 --> 01:13.163
- Oh, and look, it's the jelly pouch.
- Jelly pouch, my favorite.

01:13.206 --> 01:15.504
Still can't get enough
of the jelly pouch.

01:15.542 --> 01:19.535
<i>Just when you think you won</i>
<i>the battle, made the world safe again...</i>

01:20.713 --> 01:22.613
<i>...along comes another landmine.</i>

01:22.649 --> 01:26.210
- Are we screwing other people or not?
- What?

01:26.252 --> 01:29.881
I want to know if you're gonna go
screw O'Malley or some other loser.

01:29.923 --> 01:32.824
Then I don't cancel my plans
with the chick from Peds.

01:35.195 --> 01:38.494
You're an ass.

01:39.265 --> 01:40.493
What?

01:43.069 --> 01:45.799
- That was amazing.
- Yay.

01:46.739 --> 01:48.070
It was for me, too.

01:49.542 --> 01:53.308
- I mean, that was amazing.
- For me too!

01:56.483 --> 02:02.444
My whole life, my whole adult life,
I have been with men,

02:02.489 --> 02:07.017
and it always felt,
you know, fine, good.

02:07.060 --> 02:09.460
But I never...

02:10.763 --> 02:13.493
I mean, I did, but not...

02:13.533 --> 02:15.558
Not like this.

02:17.770 --> 02:20.568
This is like... needing glasses.

02:21.708 --> 02:25.769
- I blinded you?
- No. When I was a kid,

02:25.812 --> 02:29.248
I would get these headaches
and I went to the doctor,

02:29.282 --> 02:31.375
and they said that I needed glasses.

02:31.417 --> 02:34.284
I didn't understand that.
It didn't make sense to me

02:34.320 --> 02:37.619
because I could see fine,
and then I get the glasses

02:37.657 --> 02:41.218
and I put them on and I'm in the car
on the way home,

02:41.261 --> 02:44.094
and, suddenly, I yell...

02:46.266 --> 02:50.566
...because the big green blobs
I'd been staring at my whole life,

02:50.603 --> 02:53.299
they weren't big green blobs!

02:53.339 --> 02:57.366
They were leaves... on trees.

02:58.077 --> 03:00.238
I could see the leaves.

03:01.447 --> 03:04.007
And I didn't even know
I was missing the leaves,

03:04.050 --> 03:08.453
I didn't even know that leaves existed,
and then... leaves.

03:11.057 --> 03:13.389
You are glasses.

03:15.461 --> 03:17.861
I am so gay.

03:17.897 --> 03:20.866
I am so, so, so gay.

03:20.900 --> 03:23.095
I am extremely gay.

03:23.136 --> 03:27.232
Um...

03:29.642 --> 03:31.132
I have to go.

03:41.454 --> 03:45.254
Gentlemen, I want you to meet the new
head of trauma at Seattle Grace,

03:45.291 --> 03:48.454
Major Owen Hunt. You remember
Derek Shepherd, Mark Sloan?

03:48.494 --> 03:50.462
- He stole my patient.
- Mine too.

03:50.496 --> 03:53.659
- Now you'll get a chance to steal mine.
- Looking forward to it.

03:53.700 --> 03:55.691
I talked to a friend
of mine at the DOH.

03:55.735 --> 03:58.568
Now that we have Owen,
we are being reclassified

03:58.605 --> 04:01.836
as a level-one trauma unit
by the end of the month.

04:01.874 --> 04:03.307
That explains it.

04:03.343 --> 04:05.334
My mom bought it for me when I was five,

04:05.378 --> 04:08.905
which was a super creepy gift
for a five-year-old, but I liked it.

04:08.948 --> 04:10.040
Run!

04:18.925 --> 04:23.658
- OK, what was that all about?
- I just saw Owen. Major Owen Hunt.

04:23.696 --> 04:26.028
The guy who pulled
the icicle from my chest.

04:26.065 --> 04:29.159
- I thought he was in Iraq.
- Now he's here, in my hospital.

04:29.202 --> 04:32.933
- OK, so?
- So... So we kissed.

04:32.972 --> 04:36.499
He kissed me. It was stupid,
it was nothing. Stupid nothing.

04:36.542 --> 04:39.477
But you don't think he thinks
it was a stupid nothing.

04:39.512 --> 04:41.912
He obviously likes me, he's back.
What's he doing?

04:41.948 --> 04:45.611
Don't think he quit the military
for you? That'd be severely stalkery,

04:45.652 --> 04:46.710
but very romantic.

04:46.753 --> 04:49.654
I'm not getting involved
with another attending.

04:49.689 --> 04:52.214
Coast clear?

05:00.667 --> 05:03.158
- You paged me, chief?
- Yes, I did.

05:03.202 --> 05:07.571
'Cause generally, when I'm paged to
the helipad, there's something landing.

05:07.607 --> 05:11.543
Yeah. You pulled off a 12-person
domino surgery last week.

05:11.577 --> 05:13.909
That's the kind of thing
we need every week.

05:13.946 --> 05:17.882
It's the kind of thing that shows me
you'll be a great surgeon someday.

05:17.917 --> 05:20.477
- Well, thank you, sir.
- It's not enough.

05:20.520 --> 05:23.683
I don't want you to be just great.
I want you to be the best.

05:23.723 --> 05:27.454
If you're gonna succeed me as the
best general surgeon in this hospital,

05:27.493 --> 05:30.656
you need to start now, today,
which means you need to be me.

05:30.697 --> 05:33.222
You want to take point
on a surgery, take point.

05:33.266 --> 05:36.258
Problem comes up, solve it.
Don't talk to me, just do it.

05:36.302 --> 05:38.236
- Be me.
- Be you?

05:38.271 --> 05:39.363
Be me.

05:40.506 --> 05:41.939
I can do that.

05:42.608 --> 05:45.736
I don't know why you had to bring me
all the way up here to...

05:45.778 --> 05:49.407
That's why. Lake Washington Med
is sending over a 10-year-old girl

05:49.449 --> 05:52.418
with an abdominal leiomyosarcoma.
It's inoperable.

05:52.452 --> 05:56.821
You're gonna have to put together a team
and come up with a plan to save her.

05:57.857 --> 06:02.885
- Save a girl with an inoperable tumor?
- It isn't easy being me.

06:02.929 --> 06:04.863
What's wrong with you?

06:04.897 --> 06:06.125
What's wrong with me?

06:06.165 --> 06:09.566
We've been sleeping together
for a week and already you're bored.

06:09.602 --> 06:12.298
I'm hot and great in bed,
so what's wrong with you?

06:12.338 --> 06:16.274
